items.text: Burrito skin is good and fillings taste fresh. Good for a quick bite or takeaway.
This was my favourite place for burritos in Singapore, but since they reopened it's disappointing. The filling options are reduced, so ndercooked pinto beans & salsa verde only (no spicy salsa). Sad.
Love the burrito bowl but if you want veggies with that's it's extra for lettuce. Great for quick takeaway meals and huge servings.
Good mexican food for less
Burritos started good and have improved a lot in the past few months. Beer is a good deal there - Cheap coronas and good food make it a good way to start the evening
Pretty big sized burritos,could use a bit more cheese and guac and wasn't as spicy as I hoped for.The nachos were a little soft and probably needed more cheese in it.Overall not a bad Mexican place.
They have a special offer / promotion on Thursdays: Corona bottled beer only $2.50 with every burrito
Great burritos but they need to accelerate service speed
I've been on the hunt for good burritos in Singapore. I think this place is it! Maybe the first and only place that actually packs the burritos in foil so you can hold them while eating.
Now they have quesadillas on the menu too! Yum!
Awesome, one of best I have had!
Best Burritos in Singapore and so fairly priced!
Great area, good perch for a quick burrito-and-frozen-margarita fix. It is excellent, and a good walk to the Working Capitol co-working space round the corner.
Singapore's Chipotle
Not impressed .the pescado is not good.
Pretty good burritos. Considering that I've never been to Mexico. Or had real burritos before. But really, you're just here to look cool while eating minced meat and veg stuffed in wheat tortillas.
The best place in Singapore for burritos and nachos. Generous fillings and value for money.
Love the shit outta the pescados here jfc always coming back. I want spicier salsas tho that's the only thing.
Burritos by far the best!
Best burritos in town.
Used to be good before renovation. Now it's just meh :(
Actually, I think my favorite place for a burrito in Singapore now. Good value, and flavorful. Also, nicely modern interior design.
Love the no carb wrap!
They serve Mission-style burritos, named after d Mission District in San Francisco where this giant-sized burrito was made popular
Great burritos!
As a burrito bar, they fold d ingredients into a jumbo tortilla behind d prep counter. After paying, u eat along counter tables along d wall & to the back
As close as we can get to Chipotle and Moe's - but it's great in own right and a solid price.

I love that they give you proper glasses of water. No sippy paper cups that force you to keep asking for refills. They gave me water in a glass, brimming with ice. -- really refreshing on a hot day.<3
Get your burrito combinations ready before ordering... You wouldn't want a nasty tasting one with all the wrong choices!
It's basically a copy of Chipotle. Not that that's bad? Quesadilla is really boring; go for a burrito.
Great Mexican food... burritos!
Ok Mexican food. Nothing mind-blowing.
Amazing wraps and beautiful lighting!
Nice Mexican food. Try the habanero sauce
Love this place. How could this not have happened sooner? Singapore wake up - burritos are the future!
Good Burritos, Veggie Burrito is fine but not much variety for Veg. Cold Staff.  Cost on the high side by Big Serving.
Brilliant burritos.   Super filling so get one to share with a side of chips.
They sometimes run out of food before their kitchen closes at 11pm. Call ahead if you're travelling from afar!
Second time here - def a let down in taste and service.
Order the quesadillas!
Gets crowded at lunch (has good reason to) - Try going in the evening when it's less crowded.
When a burrito is $12 you can't go wrong! Especially when they're a good feed, taste great, and can be customised Subway style.
Beef burritos
Very Good Food! Although Guacamole is not so good. The service is incredibly slow!! If you get there and there is a queue you will be waiting a long time.
No jalapeño to an otherwise great burrito place.
OMG the California burrito.  Steak, cheese, fries and gravy.  Add some of the hot sauce for more Yums!
Try the carnita, find it more flavorful. and request them to steam the burrito else it's quite cold
Great food. Tip: order less carb and more protein and veggie. Pineapple salad is great. ^^
Simple place with decent mexican food
Delicious and big burritos! The pulled pork hits the spot.
Excellent burrito's! Cool vibe.
It was decent Mexican food, but nothing to write home about. The quesadilla is quite large - same as burrito minus rice and cheese. Would be improved with a selection of salsas and easy customisation
Check out Wings Wednesday ($0.50 a wing!) always service with a smile in Muchachos! I wish they had Gluten Free wraps but they do have the burrito bowl option yay :)
Hangover/uber-hungry lunch perfection! Delicious premium burritos where quality ingredients compose awesome confort food, with a rare balance of flavours. Try it and crave it forever after.
Really delicious burrito. Loved the chewiness of the wrap used, loved their fun menu! Wish they had steak instead of ground beef though. Opted for chicken w rice, still good!
Nice (spider) lights and yummy burritos but it's not really a place for serious gatherings and first dates.
Big portions good quality. Crowded on weekends. Top guacamole and beef burrito.
A decent burrito. They do the tortilla right, but I wish they had more extra options, like a mango or corn salsa of some sort.
😍😍🐷😋😋 &  the green chili?  Sauce
The quesadilla looks more like nicely fried prata with filling, which doesn't mean it is bad. It is actually very good!
$2.50 Corona Beer for every Burrito! Every Thirsty Thursday! 🍻 🍻
Vegetarian burrito pretty tasty. 2 tables for outdoor seating available.
Breakfast burritos are amazing. Comes with a little cup of syrup, yum! Too bad it's probably 1000+ calories otherwise would eat this every day!
Thursday special! Corona for $2.50!
They've got wifi!!! Oh, and their burritos are ok ;-)
Decent food, friendly staff! Definitely worth a try.
BURRITOS!!!!! I love everything here except for the steak one a little chewwy for me but everything else yay.
Avoid the guacamole. Freezing cold and tastes like industrial. I don't think is totally made in the house.
Good vibes
간판이 없어서 앞에서 한참 헤맴.. 와인바 바로 옆에 위치  가격이 괜츈함 맛도 나쁘지 않음. 그치만 타코는 바하타코분위기도 캐쥬얼함
One of the best burritos I had in Singapore! The steak burrito is tender and juicy, bursting with flavours and goodness with every bite. Pascare is one of my favourite here. A definite must-try!
